      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum FEA with nonlinear geometry and frictional contact must be justified by literature precedent and sensitivity analysis showing model form dominates uncertainty budget.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear geometry (large-displacement formulation) and frictional contact (μ=0.3, titanium-on-titanium) are consistent with published FDA guidance and peer-reviewed F1717 FEA literature. Sensitivity study confirmed model form uncertainty is the dominant contributor. Gradation 3 achieved."
