      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing conducted under at least two distinct load configurations or displacement rates to bracket clinical loading variability.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single ASTM F1717 standardized configuration (5° offset, 10 mm/min displacement rate). Only one test condition was evaluated, yielding Gradation 2 rather than the required Gradation 3. This factor is below the required level; compensating confidence is drawn from the large sample size and inter-laboratory consistency."
