    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The overall credibility assessment supports an Accepted decision at Medium assurance level. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is compensated by the large sample size (N=11), inter-laboratory consistency, and the standardized ASTM F1717 protocol. The Output comparison factor was assessed qualitatively based on preliminary inter-laboratory data; structured level assignments are pending final reconciliation but are not expected to alter the overall determination. The risk-informed credibility determination supports use of the FEA ensemble for regulatory submission.",
